[{'text': 'Hi YouTube, Darth Here:
This is CTE Sunday, where I run down all the', 'start': 0.38, 'duration': 3.35}, {'text': "latest changes on the Battlefield 4 Community
Test Environment. This week we've got night", 'start': 3.73, 'duration': 4.08}, {'text': 'vision changes, some significant "netcode"
upgrades, major changes to the way spotting', 'start': 7.81, 'duration': 4.32}, {'text': "works, and some minor tweaks, fixes, and corrections.
Additionally, I'll talk about upcoming changes", 'start': 12.13, 'duration': 4.969}, {'text': 'to the Community Test Enrivonment and where
we stand on the Spring Patch.', 'start': 17.099, 'duration': 3.09}, {'text': 'Night Vision
First up, there were some revisions to the', 'start': 20.189, 'duration': 1.941}, {'text': 'way that the new night vision optics work.
The first thing I noticed is that the effect', 'start': 22.13, 'duration': 3.889}, {'text': 'of the light sources on night vision has been
amped way up. Flares, flashlights, lasers,', 'start': 26.019, 'duration': 4.861}, {'text': 'and thermal grenades are now much more blinding
to night vision scopes. However, once they', 'start': 30.88, 'duration': 4.38}, {'text': 'get out of your immediate view, they become
irrelevant, so it can be managed.', 'start': 35.26, 'duration': 3.87}, {'text': "Also, if you were here last week, you'll remember
that DICE had applied a black ring to both", 'start': 39.13, 'duration': 3.78}, {'text': "night vision scopes that has now been removed
this week. Now you'll have the full vision", 'start': 42.91, 'duration': 4.03}, {'text': 'of the circular scope, but to offset this,
the blinding effects from the light sources', 'start': 46.94, 'duration': 3.76}, {'text': 'will fill more of the screen.
I think now that the night vision optics are', 'start': 50.7, 'duration': 3.47}, {'text': 'starting to come together, this will provide
a nice little interplay between blinding the', 'start': 54.17, 'duration': 3.61}, {'text': "sights and the sights users. It's a little
hard to gauge right now how that will play", 'start': 57.78, 'duration': 4.62}, {'text': "out with the low populations on the CTE server
- much ado to this week's Hardline launch.", 'start': 62.4, 'duration': 4.959}, {'text': "Spotting
Now spotting wasn't necessarily broken in", 'start': 67.359, 'duration': 2.37}, {'text': 'Battlefield 4, but it definitely could use
some improvements. First, did you know that', 'start': 69.729, 'duration': 3.621}, {'text': 'in the live version of the game: whenever
an enemy crosses the spotting cone in front', 'start': 73.35, 'duration': 3.75}, {'text': 'of your player, even if you do not spot them,
they are added to the minimap for everyone', 'start': 77.1, 'duration': 4.659}, {'text': "on your team? This cone extends for more than
a kilometer in retail - so if you've ever", 'start': 81.759, 'duration': 4.121}, {'text': 'wondered how you were spotted, there you go.
Now the changes this week reduce that distance', 'start': 85.88, 'duration': 4.259}, {'text': 'from over a kilometer to just 100 meters for
this passive spotting.', 'start': 90.139, 'duration': 3.98}, {'text': 'Additionally, the general shape of spotting
has been tweaked. Rather than being a cone', 'start': 94.119, 'duration': 3.64}, {'text': "at all distances, it's now more of a diamond.
It's the same 3 degree spot at closer ranges,", 'start': 97.759, 'duration': 5.29}, {'text': "but now at long ranges it's only .15 degrees.
The maximum distance that players and vehicles", 'start': 103.049, 'duration': 5.49}, {'text': 'can be spotted is also now 1200 meters. This
combination of effects will make it somewhat', 'start': 108.539, 'duration': 4.951}, {'text': "more difficult to mash the spot key and randomly
come up with a player you didn't actually", 'start': 113.49, 'duration': 4.239}, {'text': 'see.
Netcode', 'start': 117.729, 'duration': 0.78}, {'text': 'So there were two major components to the
"netcode" updates this week. The first was', 'start': 118.509, 'duration': 3.731}, {'text': 'an update to the way that the game handles
bullet simulation. While these are technical', 'start': 122.24, 'duration': 3.969}, {'text': 'in nature, the sum of these changes is that
the prediction being done on the client should', 'start': 126.209, 'duration': 3.861}, {'text': 'now be much closer to what is actually going
to happen on the server. The specifics of', 'start': 130.07, 'duration': 4.36}, {'text': 'which are that DICE removed some underlying
code that produced errors in the prediction', 'start': 134.43, 'duration': 3.75}, {'text': "system on the client, and implemented a simulator
on the client to match the server's processing", 'start': 138.18, 'duration': 4.84}, {'text': 'of the order of bullets. Net effect is that
predicted bullet hits should more closely', 'start': 143.02, 'duration': 4.63}, {'text': 'match the actual result and tracer fire.
The second part of the "netcode" update is', 'start': 147.65, 'duration': 4.48}, {'text': 'a huge game-changer for Battlefield. Presently
the tick rate of Battlefield 4 is locked in', 'start': 152.13, 'duration': 4.62}, {'text': 'at a maximum of 30 Hz, meaning that your client
communicates to the server up to thirty times', 'start': 156.75, 'duration': 4.59}, {'text': 'per second. DICE has now changed this tick
rate - specifically for bullets - to match', 'start': 161.34, 'duration': 4.45}, {'text': 'whatever your frame rate is. So if you have
200 frames per second, your send rate for', 'start': 165.79, 'duration': 4.69}, {'text': 'bullets will now be 200 Hz. This change will
only apply to the PC and newest generation', 'start': 170.48, 'duration': 6.08}, {'text': 'consoles.
The goal of the tickrate change is to lessen', 'start': 176.56, 'duration': 2.67}, {'text': 'the effect of damage spikes that arrive in
single packets. Remember that your game receives', 'start': 179.23, 'duration': 4.72}, {'text': 'information in packets of data that are transmitted
from the server and sometimes these packets', 'start': 183.95, 'duration': 4.45}, {'text': "are loaded full of one player's damage all
at once. Particularly this was noticeable", 'start': 188.4, 'duration': 4.65}, {'text': 'from players that were playing out of their
region or had poor connections. It also lead', 'start': 193.05, 'duration': 4.61}, {'text': 'to a lot of "one-frame deaths" from high damage
weapons like the SCAR-H, FAMAS, and other', 'start': 197.66, 'duration': 4.95}, {'text': 'weapons with fast time-to-kill. This happened
because all the damage would be sent in a', 'start': 202.61, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': 'single packet from one client, to the server,
and then to the victim.', 'start': 206.61, 'duration': 3.57}, {'text': "So that's a pretty big change and I think
it'll mean a lot for the responsiveness of", 'start': 210.18, 'duration': 3.22}, {'text': 'gun battles. But time will tell.
Miscellaneous', 'start': 213.4, 'duration': 2.51}, {'text': "As with every week, we've got a few smaller
changes that I'll cover now. Continued work", 'start': 215.91, 'duration': 3.98}, {'text': 'was put in on the night versions of Zavod
and Golmud, with lighting being the main focus', 'start': 219.89, 'duration': 4.01}, {'text': 'this week. Soldier callouts were slightly
tweaked, and a sound crash bug was also fixed.', 'start': 223.9, 'duration': 4.98}, {'text': "That's all the updates from the CTE for this
week, but we've got more coming this next", 'start': 228.88, 'duration': 3.6}, {'text': "week. There's been rumors circulating that
we will see new content coming to the CTE", 'start': 232.48, 'duration': 3.57}, {'text': 'in the coming weeks, and some folks are claiming
that it may even land this next week. However,', 'start': 236.05, 'duration': 4.46}, {'text': "without there being any social media traffic
from the usual promotional channels, I don't", 'start': 240.51, 'duration': 3.98}, {'text': "think we'll be seeing any new maps not related
to night maps for some time soon. What has", 'start': 244.49, 'duration': 4.28}, {'text': 'been mentioned is that the Spring Patch will
begin testing on the CTE very soon.', 'start': 248.77, 'duration': 4.51}, {'text': "But that's enough speculation. If you're new
around here, please take a moment to check", 'start': 253.28, 'duration': 3.35}, {'text': "out my channel and consider subscribing. As
always, thanks for watching, and I'll see", 'start': 256.63, 'duration': 3.74}, {'text': 'you next time, YouTube.', 'start': 260.37, 'duration': 1.0}]

they expanded northward,', 'start': 25.903, 'duration': 2.643}, {'text': 'adjusting to a variety of
climates, environments, and diets.', 'start': 28.546, 'duration': 2.937}, {'text': '- [Female Narrator] And
when Christopher Columbus', 'start': 31.483, 'duration': 1.373}, {'text': 'discovered America, he
discovered raccoons,', 'start': 32.856, 'duration': 2.048}, {'text': 'and the delicious tang of raccoon meat', 'start': 34.904, 'duration': 2.736}, {'text': 'on the Atlantic voyage home.', 'start': 37.64, 'duration': 1.669}, {'text': '- [Male Narrator] Since
then, raccoons have expanded', 'start': 39.309, 'duration': 1.44}, {'text': 'into Europe, Russia, and Japan.', 'start': 40.749, 'duration': 1.501}, {'text': "And they've done exceedingly
well for themselves.", 'start': 42.25, 'duration': 2.05}, {'text': '- [Female Narrator] For
instance, Kassel, Germany,', 'start': 44.3, 'duration': 1.465}, {'text': 'has the largest raccoon
population in Europe,', 'start': 45.765, 'duration': 2.546}, {'text': 'with up to 100 raccoons
per square kilometer.', 'start': 48.311, 'duration': 2.578}, {'text': "- [Male Narrator] They're
just perfectly suited", 'start': 50.889, 'duration': 1.122}, {'text': 'for urban life.', 'start': 52.011, 'duration': 0.902}, {'text': "For starters, they're
intelligent problem-solvers,", 'start': 52.913, 'duration': 1.904}, {'text': 'capable of remembering solutions to tasks', 'start': 54.817, 'duration': 1.961}, {'text': 'for up to three years.', 'start': 56.778, 'duration': 1.123}, {'text': '- [Female Narrator] Plus,
the young raccoons, or kits,', 'start': 57.901, 'duration': 1.858}, {'text': 'stay with their mothers for up to a year', 'start': 59.759, 'duration': 1.597}, {'text': 'of protection and training.', 'start': 61.356, 'duration': 1.169}, {'text': "So, when they're ready
to set out on their own,", 'start': 62.525, 'duration': 1.846}, {'text': "they already have some of
mom's street-smart secrets.", 'start': 64.371, 'duration': 3.204}, {'text': '- [Male Narrator] And as
highly adaptive omnivores,', 'start': 67.575, 'duration': 1.493}, {'text': "they're happy to chow down
on just about anything", 'start': 69.068, 'duration': 1.75}, {'text': 'they can get their hands on,
including grapes, spaghetti,', 'start': 70.818, 'duration': 2.482}, {'text': 'pet food, and good old-fashioned garbage.', 'start': 73.3, 'duration': 1.847}, {'text': '- [Female Narrator] They
have some impressive tools', 'start': 75.147, 'duration': 1.516}, {'text': 'to score those delicacies with, too.', 'start': 76.663, 'duration': 1.935}, {'text': 'Their front paws are absurdly dextrous,', 'start': 78.598, 'duration': 1.896}, {'text': 'and their heightened
sense of touch allows them', 'start': 80.494, 'duration': 2.224}, {'text': 'to detect objects, even in
dark bone-chilling conditions', 'start': 82.718, 'duration': 2.4}, {'text': 'that would leave humans numb and fumbling.', 'start': 85.118, 'duration': 2.093}, {'text': '- [Male narrator] So they
easily handle doorknobs,', 'start': 87.211, 'duration': 1.648}, {'text': 'latches, lids, and jars.', 'start': 88.859, 'duration': 1.305}, {'text': 'Factor in their teeth as well,', 'start': 90.164, 'duration': 1.259}, {'text': 'and they pretty much run the streets,', 'start': 91.423, 'duration': 1.521}, {'text': 'causing considerable damage
and nuisance in the process.', 'start': 92.944, 'duration': 2.517}, {'text': '- [Female Narrator] Today, city
raccoons tend to live longer', 'start': 95.461, 'duration': 1.941}, {'text': 'and have more offspring
than their country cousins.', 'start': 97.402, 'duration': 2.295}, {'text': 'While cats and dogs long
ago domesticated themselves', 'start': 99.697, 'duration': 2.5}, {'text': 'to benefit from life amid humans,', 'start': 102.197, 'duration': 1.943}, {'text': 'these newcomers to urban living', 'start': 104.14, 'duration': 1.728}, {'text': 'are still working out their parameters.', 'start': 105.868, 'duration': 1.872}, {'text': '- [Male Narrator] While Mark
